Gemini said*Leveling Up : Rider Tags!*






We=E2=80=99ve given *Rider Tags* a major upgrade to help you move away from=
 manual
management toward high-speed, effortless organization.


Rider tags are basically* digital labels* used to organize riders in our
system.

These tags allow the user to organize/label riders based on their unique
traits into useful groups instead of managing them one by one.


In short Rider tags are here to make your life easy!
What=E2=80=99s New




Configuring Tags

The user can create, update or delete *new or old tags* from our system.
Navigation for tags is as follows:

*Dashboard > Settings > Users & Permissions > Onboarding & KYC.*


Creating New Tags


Step by step guide on how you can create a new rider tag. Don=E2=80=99t wor=
ry its
very easy!

   -

   Click on =E2=80=98Tags=E2=80=99 section in Onboarding and KYC page
   -

   You must assign a =E2=80=98Name=E2=80=99 and a =E2=80=98Value=E2=80=99 t=
o a Tag.
   -

   Give your tag a unique name. e.g. Zone or Two wheeler Riders
   *(please make sure the name is correct cause this name is the identifier
   for the tag and cannot be changed)*
   -

   Add atleast one value for the tag. e.g. saket or Malviya nagar.
   *(Max 10 and no duplicate values are allowed)*



Thats it! you are all set.


Assigning Tags via Dashboard


You can now assign both tags to a new or existing rider via the Dashboard.



   -

   *New Rider:* While adding a new rider in the system, you can assign as
   many tags as you like. But only 1 value for each tag can be applied to t=
his
   rider.
   *Navigation =E2=86=92 Riders > New Rider*


   -

   *Existing Rider: *User can assign old or new tags to an existing rider
   from =E2=80=98Edit details=E2=80=99 screen

   *Navigation =E2=86=92 Riders > Rider Name > Rider Overview Modal > Rider=
 name >
   Edit details*





Assigning Tags via Admin App



*Navigation =E2=86=92 Home > My Riders > New Rider*

Few things to keep in mind:

   -

   The tags are configured only from the Dashboard, not Admin App.
   -

   Tags can only be assigned to a new rider during the time of new rider
   creation

What This Means To YouGemini said



   -

   *Better visibility over your assets*

   Tags act as a way to =E2=80=9Ccapture commonly observed rider characteri=
stics=E2=80=9D.


   -

   *Standardization and Data Sanitation*


   System enforces strict formatting (alphanumeric only, length validation
   on keys and values), ensuring that tags aren't just labels, but *predict=
able
   data points* that can be used for reliable reporting.


Important Note!

Multiple new and existing modules will integrate with Tags to streamline
workflows and enable a wide range of automations. To ensure seamless
operations and maximize platform efficiency, maintaining data consistency
and accuracy while configuring Tags is essential.
